description: Named in memory of Ol Pejeta’s most famous rhino ambassador, Morani’s was named one of the top 20 amazing places to eat in Kenya’! It’s not hard to see why. Conveniently located at the Information Centre, we’re the perfect halfway stop during an adventure packed day of safari and activities. Enjoy a famous Morani burger - made from Ol Pejeta beef, oozing with cheese, topped with bacon with a side of homemade fries. Light lunchers can opt for a crisp healthy salad, or a wrap to eat on the go. Kids are catered for too. All our food is homemade from the freshest ingredients, locally sourced whenever possible. Our new extensive coffee menu means we must be one of the only places in Kenya where you can get a hazelnut cappuccino in the middle of black rhino country! There's a small shop at the restaurant with great souvenirs and curios made by local craftspeople, as well as Ol Pejeta merchandise. Birthday in the bush? Morani’s can cater for groups of up to 60 people!

description:
Located less than 2 km north of Nanyuki Town along the Meru road, Kongoni Camp presents a captivating setting against the awe-inspiring slopes of Mount Kenya. Surrounded by a rich variety of indigenous forest, including olive, cedar, and remnants of other tree species, the camp exudes a serene and tranquil atmosphere. Its unique and rustic charm sets it apart, offering guests a truly immersive experience in their natural surroundings.

Despite its close proximity to the town, Kongoni Camp has been thoughtfully designed to provide a deep connection with the environment. Whether you choose to dine, enjoy a cup of coffee, or stay in our accommodations, you will find yourself immersed in the untamed beauty of the wilderness, forging a special bond with the African bush.

Embrace the serenity and natural beauty of Kongoni Camp Nanyuki as you embark on an unforgettable journey in a truly enchanting environment. We welcome you to discover the magic of our hotel resort.
